$95\\%$ of the time, we can simply use this equation:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Range}&=(\\text{average} \\pm2) \\times \\text{standard deviation}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Using this formula, we will get the range of values that we will see $95\\%$ of the time.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Range}&=(6.3\\% \\pm2) \\times 8.4\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"For the lower end,\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Range}&=(6.3\\% - 2) \\times 8.4\\%\\\\[15 pt]\n&=36.12\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"For the upper end,\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Range}&=(6.3\\% + 2) \\times 8.4\\%\\\\[15 pt]\n&=69.72\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"This means that $95\\%$ of the time, the range of the values will be between $36.12\\%-69.72\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"In order to solve for the range of values that will be seen $99\\%$ of the time, we can simply use this equation:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Range}&=(\\text{average} \\pm 3) \\times \\text{standard deviation}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"Using this formula, we will get the range of values that we will see $95\\%$ of the time.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Range}&=(6.3\\% \\pm 3) \\times 8.4\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"ha